data.name: pergolux beam
data.product:
A pergola is an open-air structure often used in gardens or patios. It consists of horizontal
beams that are attached to posts or columns and form a kind of roof. Pergolas can be made from different materials such as wood, metal or plastic and can come in different sizes and designs.

Pergolas serve primarily as sun protection and provide shade in the hot summer months. But they can also be used as a room divider and create an oasis of calm in a garden. A green, natural
atmosphere can be created with climbing plants such as vines or climbing roses.

A pergola is a wonderful addition to any garden, adding shade and beauty and creating a pleasant atmosphere.
